    {
      "id": 1,
      "title": "Standard Hardware Features",
      "text": "Thanks to its intelligent routing and connection management software, the NG800 series routers can access the networks of up to four cellular network operators simultaneously or sequentially for redundancy purposes. In all models, cellular networks supporting UMTS in the EMEA region can be accessed, with the router featuring two Gigabit Ethernet ports, one RS-232 port, one USB port, and a satellite receiver providing GNSS services. FAKRA (Fachkreis Automobil, Automobile Expert Group) type connectors have been used in antenna inputs to meet the rigorous mechanical and environmental requirements of the automotive industry. All models are CE compliant (RED) and have automotive type approval (UNECE R10, UNECE R118). All models in the NG800 series feature a dual-core central processor running at 1.3 GHz, 1 GB of RAM, a power unit with ignition sensor and input voltage ranging from 12VDC to 48VDC, and an embedded Linux operating system forming the basis of the BT infrastructure. The features of the standard NRSW (NetModule Router Software) software, which provides the expected functionality from the router, are listed below. Explore models with different capacities and capabilities."
